<i>Back to ones.</i>

4
00:00:20,591 --> 00:00:21,991
<i>Let's get it quiet, please.</i>

5
00:00:22,092 --> 00:00:23,591
<i>Everyone, stay off channel one now.</i>

6
00:00:23,692 --> 00:00:25,065
<i>This is a take, not a rehearsal.</i>

7
00:00:25,166 --> 00:00:26,890
<i>Picture is up.</i>

8
00:00:26,991 --> 00:00:28,331
<i>Camera's set.</i>

9
00:00:28,432 --> 00:00:29,662
<i>Let's roll sound!</i>

10
00:00:29,763 --> 00:00:30,993
<i>Sound speed.</i>

11
00:00:31,094 --> 00:00:33,039
<i>Let's speed cameras.</i>

12
00:00:33,140 --> 00:00:34,732
<i>Camera one speeding.</i>

13
00:00:34,833 --> 00:00:36,283
<i>Camera two speeding.</i>

14
00:00:36,384 --> 00:00:37,835
<i>"B" camera mark.</i>

15
00:00:37,936 --> 00:00:39,506
♪ I want to give it all to you ♪

16
00:00:39,607 --> 00:00:40,909
<i>"C" mark.</i>

17
00:00:41,010 --> 00:00:42,545
<i>Stunts ready?</i>

18
00:00:42,646 --> 00:00:44,181
♪ In the darkness ♪

19
00:00:44,282 --> 00:00:45,743
<i>Ready.</i>

20
00:00:45,844 --> 00:00:47,217
♪ There's so much I want to do ♪

21
00:00:47,318 --> 00:00:49,434
<i>In three, two, one, action.</i>

22
00:00:49,535 --> 00:00:51,751
♪ And tonight ♪

23
00:00:53,159 --> 00:00:55,623
♪ I want to lay it at your feet ♪

24
00:00:57,691 --> 00:00:59,264
<i>They're in almost every movie.</i>

25
00:01:00,826 --> 00:01:02,760
<i>You just don't know that they're there.</i>

26
00:01:02,861 --> 00:01:05,131
<i>'Cause that's the job.</i>

27
00:01:05,232 --> 00:01:07,501
♪ I was made for lovin' you, baby ♪

28
00:01:07,602 --> 00:01:09,635
<i>They're the unknown stunt performers.</i>

29
00:01:09,736 --> 00:01:11,769
♪ You were made for lovin' me ♪

30
00:01:11,870 --> 00:01:14,321
<i>And they get paid to do the cool stuff.</i>

31
00:01:14,422 --> 00:01:16,873
♪ And I can't get enough of you, baby ♪

32
00:01:16,974 --> 00:01:18,412
♪ Can you get enough ♪

33
00:01:18,513 --> 00:01:20,118
<i>They also get paid to take it on the chin.</i>

34
00:01:20,219 --> 00:01:21,813
♪ Tonight ♪

35
00:01:23,650 --> 00:01:26,047
<i>And everywhere else,
if you know what I mean.</i>

36
00:01:26,148 --> 00:01:28,752
♪ Feel the magic ♪

37
00:01:28,853 --> 00:01:30,974
<i>Oh, that's… that's me.</i>

38
00:01:31,075 --> 00:01:33,196
<i>Colt Seavers.</i>

39
00:01:33,297 --> 00:01:35,430
<i>Getting blown up and hiding
my face in a muddy puddle.</i>

40
00:01:35,531 --> 00:01:37,134
<i>Which isn't ideal…</i>

41
00:01:37,235 --> 00:01:39,763
<i>when you're trying to look cool
in front of Jody.</i>

42
00:01:39,864 --> 00:01:42,315
<i>Who you just so happen
to have a major crush on.</i>

43
00:01:42,416 --> 00:01:44,867
<i>She's a camera operator.</i>

44
00:01:44,968 --> 00:01:46,721
P.A. Looking
for Tom Ryder's stunt double.

45
00:01:46,822 --> 00:01:48,574
<i>She's definitely gonna achieve her goal…</i>

46
00:01:48,675 --> 00:01:50,313
<i>of being a big-time
Hollywood movie director.</i>

47
00:01:50,414 --> 00:01:52,039
You're so uncoordinated.

48
00:01:52,140 --> 00:01:54,151
<i>I don't want to
overromanticize it or anything…</i>

49
00:01:54,252 --> 00:01:56,946
<i>but I think what Jody and I
got's the kind of thing…</i>

50
00:01:57,047 --> 00:01:58,585
<i>you can only really find in the movies.</i>

51
00:01:58,686 --> 00:02:00,079
- Hey. Jody.
- Thank you.

52
00:02:00,180 --> 00:02:01,917
Hey, Colt. Thanks so much
for the stunt chat.

53
00:02:02,018 --> 00:02:04,325
Stunt chats. I love 'em. Anytime.

54
00:02:04,426 --> 00:02:06,163
Hey, uh, Tom needs to see you
at the monitor.

55
00:02:06,264 --> 00:02:07,824
- Uh-oh.
- Yeah.

56
00:02:07,925 --> 00:02:09,088
Am I in trouble?

57
00:02:09,189 --> 00:02:10,892
<i>She's talking about Tom Ryder…</i>

58
00:02:10,993 --> 00:02:13,599
<i>who happens to be the biggest
action star on the pl…</i>

59
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:15,237
<i>Wait, why am I explaining this?</i>

60
00:02:15,338 --> 00:02:18,141
<i>You know who Tom Ryder is.
He's Tom Ryder.</i>

61
00:02:18,242 --> 00:02:21,101
<i>Anyway, I've been his
stunt double for six years now.</i>

62
00:02:21,202 --> 00:02:24,105
Uh… flying in.

63
00:02:28,782 --> 00:02:30,314
What happened? What's up?

64
00:02:30,415 --> 00:02:31,983
Guess we're going again.

65
00:02:32,084 --> 00:02:33,651
You know Tom and Gail.

66
00:02:33,752 --> 00:02:35,989
There's a lot of grumbling
and a bunch of hand gestures…

67
00:02:36,090 --> 00:02:38,327
over at the monitor, so I'm
not sure what's going on there…

68
00:02:38,428 --> 00:02:40,297
- but…
- Let me guess… too much face.

69
00:02:41,399 --> 00:02:43,661
Okay, guys. Go to one for me.

70
00:02:43,762 --> 00:02:45,200
Um…

71
00:02:45,301 --> 00:02:46,999
- Jody, right?
- What's your name again?

72
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:48,797
As you can see, that is not my chin.

73
00:02:48,898 --> 00:02:51,031
When you look at my face, look
at my jaw compared to his jaw…

74
00:02:51,132 --> 00:02:52,702
it's like his chin is off.

75
00:02:52,803 --> 00:02:53,869
- It's like…
- Yeah, we can't replace his face.

76
00:02:53,970 --> 00:02:55,540
It's like Mr. Potato Head.

77
00:02:55,641 --> 00:02:57,542
- I mean, no offense or anything, but you know.
- Oh…

78
00:02:57,643 --> 00:02:59,545
Oh, yeah, no. Sorry, I got lost
in your beautiful jawline.

79
00:02:59,646 --> 00:03:01,277
- It's dreamy.
- No, listen…

80
00:03:01,378 --> 00:03:03,111
we're just saying it's not working for us.

81
00:03:03,212 --> 00:03:04,946
- Let's, uh…
- Okay.

82
00:03:05,047 --> 00:03:06,485
Let's go again.

83
00:03:06,586 --> 00:03:07,685
Oh, yeah, no,
we're gonna have to go again.

84
00:03:07,786 --> 00:03:09,521
- Okay. Okay.
- Yeah. 100%.

85
00:03:09,622 --> 00:03:10,985
I don't know, man. Do you think, um…

86
00:03:11,086 --> 00:03:12,854
Try and make some magic?

87
00:03:12,955 --> 00:03:14,890
Maybe you could do it backwards
or something? I don't know.

88
00:03:14,991 --> 00:03:17,056
- It's just… less face.
- Yeah.

89
00:03:17,157 --> 00:03:18,531
<i>The woman freebasing the Diet Coke…</i>

90
00:03:18,632 --> 00:03:20,565
<i>is Tom's producer Gail.</i>

91
00:03:20,666 --> 00:03:22,116
<i>- She's been making him look good for years.</i>
- Thank you.

92
00:03:22,217 --> 00:03:23,667
<i>- And it's not always easy.</i>
- All right.

93
00:03:23,768 --> 00:03:25,164
- Give me some.
- - Oh! I'm gonna…

94
00:03:25,265 --> 00:03:26,372
<i>I can't complain.</i>

95
00:03:26,473 --> 00:03:27,638
<i>I'm working with my dream girl.</i>

96
00:03:27,739 --> 00:03:29,210
Mm.

97
00:03:29,311 --> 00:03:30,893
<i>- On my dream job.</i>
- Copy. - Go back to one.

98
00:03:30,994 --> 00:03:32,576
We got to switch
the pick points to the front.

99
00:03:32,677 --> 00:03:34,545
<i>- I'm living the dream.</i>
- He wants to go again.

100
00:03:34,646 --> 00:03:36,317
- Copy that, Colt. We'll flip the rig.
- Thank you.

101
00:03:36,418 --> 00:03:37,977
You'll be falling backwards.

102
00:03:38,078 --> 00:03:39,749
- Jody, go to two.
- Stand quiet, please.

103
00:03:39,850 --> 00:03:41,554
Everyone, stay off channel one now.

104
00:03:42,656 --> 00:03:44,489
Do you have a question for me?

105
00:03:44,590 --> 00:03:46,426
Uh, yeah. It just looked
just now like you wanted…

106
00:03:46,527 --> 00:03:48,185
- to ask me something.
- Oh.

107
00:03:48,286 --> 00:03:50,226
I was gonna go for
a spicy margarita after work.

108
00:03:50,327 --> 00:03:52,367
I was wondering
if you drink spicy margaritas.

109
00:03:54,699 --> 00:03:56,749
Um, well, just to keep it professional…

110
00:03:56,850 --> 00:03:58,899
I can only have one spicy margarita.

111
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,903
Because if I have two,
I start making bad decisions.

112
00:04:02,004 --> 00:04:03,740
Well, you know, drinking margaritas…

113
00:04:03,841 --> 00:04:06,545
is all about making bad decisions.

114
00:04:06,646 --> 00:04:08,711
Which reminds me, um…

115
00:04:08,812 --> 00:04:11,664
after this job, I-I got to go
sit on the sand somewhere…

116
00:04:11,765 --> 00:04:14,618
and I was wondering, uh…
I was gonna ask you a question.

117
00:04:14,719 --> 00:04:16,214
Tell me.

118
00:04:17,316 --> 00:04:19,690
Do you have any towels
that I can borrow?

119
00:04:21,021 --> 00:04:22,427
Yeah, I have some towels.

120
00:04:22,528 --> 00:04:24,288
You know, it's so dangerous
to swim alone.

121
00:04:25,894 --> 00:04:28,093
Well, I would ask you to,
you know, be my swim buddy…

122
00:04:28,194 --> 00:04:30,094
but I don't know
if you have a bathing suit.

123
00:04:30,195 --> 00:04:33,472
Wait a second. What do you
call that across the pond?

124
00:04:33,573 --> 00:04:36,509
We call it a swimming costume.

125
00:04:38,358 --> 00:04:40,104
Imagine that.

126
00:04:40,205 --> 00:04:42,106
After this, you and I could both be…

127
00:04:42,207 --> 00:04:44,912
on the beach somewhere
in swimming costumes…

128
00:04:45,013 --> 00:04:46,715
drinking spicy margaritas…

129
00:04:46,816 --> 00:04:49,081
- making bad decisions.
- Okay, good to go.

130
00:04:49,182 --> 00:04:50,919
Imagine that.

131
00:04:52,428 --> 00:04:54,086
Okay, let's keep it locked up all around!

132
00:04:56,220 --> 00:04:58,288
- Let's strap him in.
- Everyone quiet, please!

133
00:04:59,632 --> 00:05:01,291
Speed on "A."

134
00:05:04,197 --> 00:05:06,470
- You all right?
- All right, let's take him to ones.

135
00:05:06,571 --> 00:05:09,772
- Tail slate.
- Going to ones. - Go ahead and sit back for me.

136
00:05:11,039 --> 00:05:12,443
Let's go hot on stunts.

137
00:05:12,544 --> 00:05:14,610
- And going out to the edge.
- Stunts is hot.

138
00:05:14,711 --> 00:05:17,228
- Take up the slack.
- How we doing up there, stunt?

139
00:05:17,329 --> 00:05:19,947
- Great. He's great. Here we go.
- Position down.

140
00:05:20,983 --> 00:05:22,818
He's at ones.

141
00:05:24,415 --> 00:05:26,403
Ready to drop the line for me?

142
00:05:26,504 --> 00:05:28,492
And three, two, one.

143
00:05:28,593 --> 00:05:31,255
Action, action, action, action, action!

144
00:05:36,094 --> 00:05:38,266
Call the medic! Medic!

145
00:05:42,267 --> 00:05:44,199
Colt, are you okay?

146
00:05:44,300 --> 00:05:45,674
I need you to step back.

147
00:05:45,775 --> 00:05:47,743
You're not helping.

148
00:06:05,994 --> 00:06:07,497
<i>What's that saying…</i>

149
00:06:07,598 --> 00:06:08,894
<i>"Pride comes before the fall"?</i>

150
00:06:08,995 --> 00:06:10,291
<i>Well, they don't mention…</i>

151
00:06:10,392 --> 00:06:12,768
<i>that it sticks around afterwards, too.</i>

152
00:06:14,429 --> 00:06:16,331
<i>Jody tried so hard to be there for me.</i>

153
00:06:16,432 --> 00:06:18,019
<i>She really did. I just…</i>

154
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:19,806
<i>I couldn't do it.</i>

155
00:06:22,678 --> 00:06:25,010
<i>Then I just disappeared completely.</i>

156
00:06:27,014 --> 00:06:28,748
<i>Well…</i>

157
00:06:28,849 --> 00:06:31,379
<i>at least I thought I did.</i>

158
00:06:40,631 --> 00:06:42,015
Hello?

159
00:06:42,116 --> 00:06:43,555
Oh! Colt!

160
00:06:43,656 --> 00:06:45,094
It's Gail.

161
00:06:45,195 --> 00:06:48,081
- Your favorite producer.
- How'd you get this number?

162
00:06:48,182 --> 00:06:51,068
Someone said you were working
at the Captain's Cockatoo.

163
00:06:51,169 --> 00:06:52,200
A valet.

164
00:06:52,301 --> 00:06:54,411
Wow! I didn't believe it.

165
00:06:54,512 --> 00:06:57,376
It's actually El Cacatúa del Capitan.

166
00:06:57,477 --> 00:07:00,014
It's a family-run place. We pool tips.

167
00:07:02,552 --> 00:07:04,948
<i>Plus, I get all the burritos I can eat.</i>

168
00:07:05,049 --> 00:07:06,852
<i>Kind of living the dream
if you think about it.</i>

169
00:07:06,953 --> 00:07:09,217
Break time's over. You've got a customer.

170
00:07:09,318 --> 00:07:10,790
Number 43.

171
00:07:11,892 --> 00:07:13,860
Hey.

172
00:07:15,666 --> 00:07:17,863
Yo, bro, I know you from somewhere.

173
00:07:17,964 --> 00:07:19,567
Where I know you from, bro?

174
00:07:19,668 --> 00:07:23,033
Oh, yeah, you were on
that Tom Ryder movie I was on.

175
00:07:23,134 --> 00:07:25,232
- You're the stunt guy!
- Not anymore.

176
00:07:25,333 --> 00:07:28,686
- Did you, like, break your back or some shit?
- I did, yeah.

177
00:07:28,787 --> 00:07:32,141
I know things haven't been easy
for you since… the incident.

178
00:07:32,242 --> 00:07:33,779
And I just hope…

179
00:07:33,880 --> 00:07:36,513
that you don't hold it against me or Tom.

180
00:07:36,614 --> 00:07:39,247
You know, we were
absolutely devastated.

181
00:07:39,348 --> 00:07:40,755
He sent you a message, right?

182
00:07:43,188 --> 00:07:44,383
The prayer hands emoji?

183
00:07:44,484 --> 00:07:46,588
Right, yeah. He's still an asshole.

184
00:07:46,689 --> 00:07:48,543
How are you even still alive? Yo, babe.

185
00:07:48,644 --> 00:07:50,498
- Babe, hey, come here.
- I don't know.

186
00:07:50,599 --> 00:07:51,797
- I wish I wasn't right now.
- You got to meet this guy.

187
00:07:51,898 --> 00:07:53,292
Come here. You got to hear this.

188
00:07:53,393 --> 00:07:55,163
You don't have to hear this. It's fine. Hi.

189
00:07:55,264 --> 00:07:56,735
This dude was on a movie I was on.

190
00:07:56,836 --> 00:08:00,838
- Most epic fail I've ever seen.
- Mm.

191
00:08:00,939 --> 00:08:02,511
<i>I don't blame either one of you, Gail.</i>

192
00:08:02,612 --> 00:08:04,006
That was my fault.

193
00:08:04,107 --> 00:08:05,811
And when you start
making mistakes like that…

194
00:08:05,912 --> 00:08:07,240
it's time to hang up the pads.

195
00:08:07,341 --> 00:08:08,946
Oh, it was an accident, Colt.

196
00:08:09,047 --> 00:08:11,079
Everybody knows that.

197
00:08:11,180 --> 00:08:15,447
Tom has put me
in a real situation here, Colt.

198
00:08:15,548 --> 00:08:18,202
I just need a little bit
of help from an old friend…

199
00:08:18,303 --> 00:08:20,958
who just happens to be,
you know, the best stuntman…

200
00:08:21,059 --> 00:08:22,761
I've ever worked with in my life.

201
00:08:22,862 --> 00:08:25,160
Which is why you are getting
on a plane for me tomorrow…

202
00:08:25,261 --> 00:08:26,765
and coming to Sydney.

203
00:08:26,866 --> 00:08:28,503
I'm not getting on a plane, Gail.

204
00:08:28,604 --> 00:08:30,505
I can't bear that you would
throw away all that talent.

205
00:08:30,606 --> 00:08:32,935
You shouldn't be parking cars, Colt.

206
00:08:33,036 --> 00:08:35,609
You need to be smashing
burning Kawasakis…

207
00:08:35,710 --> 00:08:36,841
through panes of glass.

208
00:08:36,942 --> 00:08:39,205
Yo, fall guy? Yo.

209
00:08:39,306 --> 00:08:41,862
Bring my car back without a scratch…

210
00:08:41,963 --> 00:08:44,619
I got a crispy fiver here for you, bro.

211
00:09:07,006 --> 00:09:09,005
Come on. It's gonna be like old times.

212
00:09:09,106 --> 00:09:10,677
I know you've missed it.

213
00:09:10,778 --> 00:09:12,007
Goodbye, Gail.

214
00:09:12,108 --> 00:09:14,008
Wait, wait, wait! Wait. Hold on.

215
00:09:14,109 --> 00:09:15,928
Did I, did I tell you… I… Did I tell you…

216
00:09:16,029 --> 00:09:17,848
that the director's
asked for you specifically?

217
00:09:17,949 --> 00:09:19,475
Sorry to disappoint him.

218
00:09:19,576 --> 00:09:21,379
- Well, don't you want to know who it is?
- Nope.

219
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:23,590
♪ Ah-ah-ah-ah ♪

220
00:09:23,691 --> 00:09:25,481
It's Jody.

221
00:09:25,582 --> 00:09:28,353
♪ Ah-ah-ah-ah, thunder ♪

222
00:09:28,454 --> 00:09:29,562
♪ Ah-ah-ah-ah ♪

223
00:09:29,663 --> 00:09:31,410
I'm giving her her big break.

224
00:09:31,511 --> 00:09:33,088
Make sure it's an aisle seat.

225
00:09:33,189 --> 00:09:34,866
♪ Ah-ah-ah-ah, thunder ♪

226
00:09:35,966 --> 00:09:37,031
<i>I don't know.</i>

227
00:09:37,132 --> 00:09:38,494
<i>Maybe I just spent so much time…</i>

228
00:09:38,595 --> 00:09:40,067
<i>riding shotgun in someone else's story…</i>

229
00:09:40,168 --> 00:09:42,906
<i>I forgot how to take the wheel of my own.</i>

230
00:09:43,007 --> 00:09:44,304
<i>Wait. Does that make sense?</i>

231
00:09:45,976 --> 00:09:48,614
♪ Ah-ah-ah-ah ♪

232
00:09:48,715 --> 00:09:51,882
<i>I don't know why
I'm talking so much anyway.</i>

233
00:09:51,983 --> 00:09:53,949
<i>I'm not the hero of this story.</i>

234
00:09:54,050 --> 00:09:56,722
<i>I'm just the stunt guy.</i>

235
00:09:58,774 --> 00:10:00,825
♪ Thunder ♪

236
00:10:02,356 --> 00:10:04,422
♪ Thunderstruck ♪

237
00:10:05,590 --> 00:10:07,929
♪ Thunderstruck ♪

238
00:10:08,030 --> 00:10:11,495
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah, thunderstruck ♪

239
00:10:12,498 --> 00:10:15,400
♪ Ooh, thunderstruck ♪

240
00:10:19,538 --> 00:10:21,406
♪ Yeah ♪

241
00:10:26,182 --> 00:10:28,182
♪ I was shaking at the knees ♪

242
00:10:30,548 --> 00:10:31,889
No!

243
00:10:37,523 --> 00:10:40,061
Chill! It's a rental!

244
