This is a man who spent 23 minutes…

1729
01:20:21,978 --> 01:20:23,505
ushering a cockroach
out of my room once…

1730
01:20:23,606 --> 01:20:24,881
and I was like, "Just stomp
on it," and he was like…

1731
01:20:24,982 --> 01:20:26,674
"No, let it live." I mean, it's Colt.

1732
01:20:26,775 --> 01:20:28,312
I told them all of that.

1733
01:20:28,413 --> 01:20:30,986
I told him who he is…
who I thought he was.

1734
01:20:31,087 --> 01:20:32,348
Did you, emphatically?

1735
01:20:32,449 --> 01:20:33,888
- Yes, I did.
- Yeah, because he…

1736
01:20:33,989 --> 01:20:35,858
was at the airport where you sent him.

1737
01:20:35,959 --> 01:20:37,683
He never got on the plane, Jody.

1738
01:20:37,784 --> 01:20:39,339
- How many movies have we done?
- Oh, I don't know.

1739
01:20:39,440 --> 01:20:40,994
How many? Yeah, too many
to count, that's right.

1740
01:20:41,095 --> 01:20:43,030
- Yeah.
- 'Cause I put you in the contract, didn't I?

1741
01:20:43,131 --> 01:20:44,614
I put you there, right there.

1742
01:20:44,715 --> 01:20:46,197
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah? That's right…

1743
01:20:46,298 --> 01:20:47,562
- I had the assistant, the makeup and hair…
- Right.

1744
01:20:47,663 --> 01:20:49,167
…uh, trainer, and then boom…

1745
01:20:49,268 --> 01:20:51,417
Ryder's number one stuntman,
Colt Seavers.

1746
01:20:51,518 --> 01:20:53,667
That was me, I did
that. I did that for you.

1747
01:20:53,768 --> 01:20:56,109
What are you gonna do for me? Huh?

1748
01:20:56,210 --> 01:20:58,078
Die, I guess?

1749
01:20:58,179 --> 01:21:00,046
Right? Die?

1750
01:21:00,147 --> 01:21:01,576
- Is that the plan?
- It's nothing personal.

1751
01:21:01,677 --> 01:21:03,011
Oh, my God. Well, I'm taking it personal.

1752
01:21:03,112 --> 01:21:04,598
- Yeah, I can see that.
- The torture.

1753
01:21:04,699 --> 01:21:06,184
You know what? It's just business.

1754
01:21:06,285 --> 01:21:07,582
- The drugging, the Taser.
- You know, it's just business.

1755
01:21:07,683 --> 01:21:09,121
I mean, Tom Ryder's a global brand.

1756
01:21:09,222 --> 01:21:11,574
- I'm taking it personal.
- I literally move markets.

1757
01:21:11,675 --> 01:21:14,851
If I go down…
the freakin' Dow goes down.

1758
01:21:14,952 --> 01:21:18,130
If you break your back,
I replace you like this. Boom.

1759
01:21:18,231 --> 01:21:20,181
You know, if you'd just stuck to your job…

1760
01:21:20,282 --> 01:21:22,232
instead of trying to hog the spotlight…

1761
01:21:22,333 --> 01:21:24,218
this wouldn't have happened.
I mean, Henry wouldn't be…

1762
01:21:24,319 --> 01:21:26,204
on the scene, his accident
wouldn't have happened…

1763
01:21:26,305 --> 01:21:28,387
your accident… freaky little fall.

1764
01:21:28,488 --> 01:21:30,571
'Cause you just push my buttons, man.

1765
01:21:30,672 --> 01:21:32,024
Wait a second. What?

1766
01:21:33,378 --> 01:21:35,707
What?

1767
01:21:35,808 --> 01:21:38,050
What did you say about my accident?

1768
01:21:38,151 --> 01:21:39,920
Well, you know,
you pushed me over the edge.

1769
01:21:40,021 --> 01:21:41,923
You literally pushed a button.
I mean, you didn't…

1770
01:21:42,024 --> 01:21:44,520
<i>I mean, I pushed the button.</i>

1771
01:21:47,932 --> 01:21:50,691
<i>I had to crank it up a notch.</i>

1772
01:21:57,469 --> 01:21:58,807
That was you?

1773
01:21:58,908 --> 01:22:00,535
Yeah.

1774
01:22:03,947 --> 01:22:06,077
Had to teach you a little lesson, didn't I?

1775
01:22:06,178 --> 01:22:08,080
Got a little too big for your boots…

1776
01:22:08,181 --> 01:22:09,575
didn't you?

1777
01:22:09,676 --> 01:22:11,117
Henry's no different, you know.

1778
01:22:12,514 --> 01:22:15,582
Hey. You do your own stunts?

1779
01:22:15,683 --> 01:22:17,187
Do I do my own stunts?

1780
01:22:17,288 --> 01:22:19,828
In front of all those people,
that's humiliating.

1781
01:22:19,929 --> 01:22:21,996
And yeah, I'm gonna
kick you into next week.

1782
01:22:24,264 --> 01:22:27,098
But then Gail, you know…

1783
01:22:27,199 --> 01:22:29,150
- Remember Gail, right?
- I've known her for 15 years.

1784
01:22:29,251 --> 01:22:30,973
Oh, yeah. I forget, 'cause
you've been out of the game…

1785
01:22:31,074 --> 01:22:32,797
- so long, you know?
- I introduced the two of you.

1786
01:22:32,898 --> 01:22:34,304
Calls me up and says,
"It doesn't look good."

1787
01:22:34,405 --> 01:22:36,877
Bad for marketing and renting…

1788
01:22:36,978 --> 01:22:39,111
and blah, blah, blah, and murder and…

1789
01:22:39,212 --> 01:22:41,276
I know, I-I-I d…

1790
01:22:41,377 --> 01:22:45,050
I real… I really don't need this right now.

1791
01:22:45,151 --> 01:22:47,018
Fucking Henry!

1792
01:22:47,119 --> 01:22:49,120
Don't worry about it.

1793
01:22:49,221 --> 01:22:51,352
You lay low…

1794
01:22:51,453 --> 01:22:53,092
and I will handle everything.

1795
01:22:54,458 --> 01:22:57,458
Maybe we don't know people
as well as we think we do.

1796
01:22:57,559 --> 01:23:00,000
- Oh, my God.
- You know?

1797
01:23:00,959 --> 01:23:01,967
Oh, my God, it's Colt.

1798
01:23:02,068 --> 01:23:03,397
- Give me the phone.
- No.

1799
01:23:03,498 --> 01:23:05,069
- What are you doing?
- Gail, get off the pho…

1800
01:23:05,170 --> 01:23:06,533
- Oh! What are you doing?
- Oh, my… Jesus Christ, Gail!

1801
01:23:06,634 --> 01:23:09,008
- Oh, my… Oh, I'm so sorry.
- Oh, my God.

1802
01:23:09,109 --> 01:23:10,470
- Let me help you.
- No, stop it.

1803
01:23:10,571 --> 01:23:11,703
- Let me take it up to…
- Do you know what?

1804
01:23:11,804 --> 01:23:12,836
- Just give me a minute.
- Yep.

1805
01:23:12,937 --> 01:23:14,524
Just give me a minute.

1806
01:23:14,625 --> 01:23:16,313
- Yep.
- Come on.

1807
01:23:17,283 --> 01:23:19,413
This plan was so simple.

1808
01:23:19,514 --> 01:23:21,845
Yeah, we were gonna put
Henry's body on ice…

1809
01:23:21,946 --> 01:23:23,582
so it doesn't decompose.

1810
01:23:23,683 --> 01:23:26,255
We could pull you out from
that rock you crawled under.

1811
01:23:26,356 --> 01:23:28,390
- My life, yep.
- You know, scan your face.

1812
01:23:30,229 --> 01:23:32,228
Dressy here is gonna stick you
on the murder video.

1813
01:23:32,329 --> 01:23:33,932
Drug you, drive you and Henry's body…

1814
01:23:34,033 --> 01:23:36,859
off the Sydney Harbour Bridge,
in your car… boom.

1815
01:23:36,960 --> 01:23:38,762
You got murder, suicide.

1816
01:23:38,863 --> 01:23:40,549
Cut. Check the gate.

1817
01:23:40,650 --> 01:23:42,336
Move on. Beautiful.

1818
01:23:42,437 --> 01:23:44,273
I think we have different ideas
of what simple is.

1819
01:23:44,374 --> 01:23:46,005
Y-You just didn't stay down, did you?

1820
01:23:46,106 --> 01:23:47,738
You had to, like, uh, create a big scene…

1821
01:23:47,839 --> 01:23:49,442
like Colt Seavers does.

1822
01:23:49,543 --> 01:23:51,675
You could… But you know what?
This can still work…

1823
01:23:51,776 --> 01:23:55,450
because we got the murder,
now we just need the suicide.

1824
01:23:58,453 --> 01:24:00,288
- Sad.
- It's plot heavy.

1825
01:24:00,389 --> 01:24:02,191
We're getting tangled in exposition.

1826
01:24:02,292 --> 01:24:04,094
Lose the last part… the suicide.

1827
01:24:04,195 --> 01:24:06,064
You lose the audience
if there's too much.

1828
01:24:06,165 --> 01:24:07,459
Colt.

1829
01:24:07,560 --> 01:24:09,747
Where's the phone?

1830
01:24:09,848 --> 01:24:12,035
Tom, you need carbs!

1831
01:24:12,136 --> 01:24:15,269
Your brain runs on glucose!

1832
01:24:15,370 --> 01:24:17,871
For simple cognitive functions.

1833
01:24:17,972 --> 01:24:20,473
- You need them.
- Colt, you're the fall guy.

1834
01:24:20,574 --> 01:24:22,640
You're the fall guy, you know.

1835
01:24:22,741 --> 01:24:25,279
Where's the phone?

1836
01:24:25,380 --> 01:24:27,579
I mean, I… You can keep
taking hits all night…

1837
01:24:27,680 --> 01:24:29,118
but you know what?

1838
01:24:29,219 --> 01:24:31,918
I can think of a few
other people who can't.

1839
01:24:32,019 --> 01:24:34,718
We could bring Dan up here,
maybe Jody, perhaps.

1840
01:24:34,819 --> 01:24:36,753
I mean, I like Jody, but you know.

1841
01:24:36,854 --> 01:24:39,062
There's no phone.

1842
01:24:39,163 --> 01:24:40,625
Okay? That's the twist.

1843
01:24:40,726 --> 01:24:42,065
No phone.

1844
01:24:42,166 --> 01:24:44,893
He shot it out of my hand.

1845
01:24:44,994 --> 01:24:46,465
Up there, go check.

1846
01:24:46,566 --> 01:24:49,006
You, too, all of you. I'll wait.

1847
01:24:49,107 --> 01:24:51,640
- He shot it.
- You didn't know you did that?

1848
01:24:51,741 --> 01:24:54,275
It's crazy. I've been wanting
to tell you this whole time.

1849
01:24:54,376 --> 01:24:55,605
No, he didn't.

1850
01:24:55,706 --> 01:24:57,706
- I was by the door frame.
- No.

1851
01:24:57,807 --> 01:24:59,808
And he shoots it out of my hands!

1852
01:24:59,909 --> 01:25:01,347
- No.
- Take the ties off.

1853
01:25:01,448 --> 01:25:03,250
- Oh, my God, what a relief.
- That's crazy.

1854
01:25:03,351 --> 01:25:05,451
You were right about one thing,
that was the only thing…

1855
01:25:05,552 --> 01:25:07,970
keeping you alive.

1856
01:25:08,071 --> 01:25:10,488
I really wish you could see…

1857
01:25:10,589 --> 01:25:11,919
what Jody's gonna do with <i>Metalstorm.</i>

1858
01:25:12,020 --> 01:25:13,425
It's gonna be awesome.

1859
01:25:13,526 --> 01:25:17,233
And honestly… it's gonna be a banger.

1860
01:25:18,500 --> 01:25:20,367
Not so cocky now, are you, mate?

1861
01:25:20,468 --> 01:25:22,898
Jesus, Mike Mike, put a lid on it.

1862
01:25:27,344 --> 01:25:29,310
Wish you didn't break that bond, bro.

1863
01:25:29,411 --> 01:25:30,871
Wish you didn't break that bond.

1864
01:25:30,972 --> 01:25:33,281
All right, stuntman,
time for a drink, mate. Eh?

1865
01:25:33,382 --> 01:25:36,316
There we go. Eh?

1866
01:25:36,417 --> 01:25:37,976
Help!

1867
01:25:38,077 --> 01:25:39,764
Help!

1868
01:25:39,865 --> 01:25:41,552
- Shut up. Shut up.
- Help!

1869
01:25:41,653 --> 01:25:43,654
Shut up, mate.

1870
01:25:52,170 --> 01:25:53,530
There.

1871
01:25:53,631 --> 01:25:55,171
This fire gag's real.

1872
01:26:09,880 --> 01:26:11,318
Come on, guys, start the boat.

1873
01:26:11,419 --> 01:26:12,784
He's gone the wrong way.

1874
01:26:25,235 --> 01:26:26,663
Shit!

1875
01:27:37,932 --> 01:27:39,365
Oh, Colt.

1876
01:27:39,466 --> 01:27:40,899
Colt?

1877
01:27:41,000 --> 01:27:42,275
- Hey.
- What's going on?

1878
01:27:42,376 --> 01:27:43,308
What'd you sing?

1879
01:27:43,409 --> 01:27:45,177
- What?
- At karaoke.

1880
01:27:45,278 --> 01:27:46,575
- I'm sorry I didn't make it.
- It doesn't matter.

1881
01:27:46,676 --> 01:27:48,192
Listen. Everyone's saying
you killed Henry.

1882
01:27:48,293 --> 01:27:49,808
- What's happening?
- Oh, that's not true.

1883
01:27:49,909 --> 01:27:51,981
You're gonna hear a lot
of things that aren't true.

1884
01:27:52,082 --> 01:27:54,153
I just wanted to say that
when I first got here…

1885
01:27:54,254 --> 01:27:56,255
when you asked how I was doing
and I gave you the thumbs-up…

1886
01:27:56,356 --> 01:27:57,817
when you were like,
"That's stunt guy bullshit…"

1887
01:27:57,918 --> 01:28:00,082
and you're right, it's total cliché…

1888
01:28:00,183 --> 01:28:01,854
but, you know,
there's a reason you don't see…

1889
01:28:01,955 --> 01:28:03,725
the thumbs-down stunt guy.

1890
01:28:05,630 --> 01:28:08,267
You know, it's kind
of part of our training.

1891
01:28:08,368 --> 01:28:10,797
Right? You know, you get hit by a car…

1892
01:28:10,898 --> 01:28:12,303
you get thrown out of a window…

1893
01:28:12,404 --> 01:28:14,207
you get set on fire,
you give the thumbs-up.

1894
01:28:14,308 --> 01:28:16,670
But, uh, after my accident…

1895
01:28:16,771 --> 01:28:20,675
turns out was not an accident,
by the way…

1896
01:28:20,776 --> 01:28:23,545
I, uh…

1897
01:28:23,646 --> 01:28:25,450
I wasn't okay.

1898
01:28:26,453 --> 01:28:29,337
And not because I broke my back…

1899
01:28:29,438 --> 01:28:32,323
because I just felt like a huge…

1900
01:28:32,424 --> 01:28:34,188
failure.

1901
01:28:37,254 --> 01:28:39,407
And I realized that, uh…

1902
01:28:39,508 --> 01:28:41,662
you know, I'm not invincible.

1903
01:28:41,763 --> 01:28:43,467
Huge shocker.

1904
01:28:44,668 --> 01:28:47,371
And I thought maybe I wasn't so special…

1905
01:28:47,472 --> 01:28:49,163
or something, so I, uh…

1906
01:28:49,264 --> 01:28:51,869
just figured that
the thumbs-down version of me…

1907
01:28:51,970 --> 01:28:54,471
wasn't what you got
into it for, so I disappeared.

1908
01:28:54,572 --> 01:28:57,073
But, you know, I didn't
just disappear on you.

1909
01:28:57,174 --> 01:29:00,383
Uh… just disappeared on…

1910
01:29:00,484 --> 01:29:04,983
on, uh, myself… too.

1911
01:29:06,723 --> 01:29:08,424
Anyway, I'm sorry.

1912
01:29:08,525 --> 01:29:10,426
You deserved more than that. I'm sorry.

1913
01:29:10,527 --> 01:29:12,792
I just wanted you to be honest.

1914
01:29:13,861 --> 01:29:17,225
You know, honestly, it, uh, all hurts.

1915
01:29:22,639 --> 01:29:24,901
Getting hit by a car hurts.

1916
01:29:25,002 --> 01:29:26,903
Getting thrown out of a window hurts.

1917
01:29:27,004 --> 01:29:31,040
Getting set on fire really hurts.

1918
01:29:31,141 --> 01:29:33,609
But, uh…

1919
01:29:37,588 --> 01:29:39,918
none of it ever hurt as much
as not being with you.

1920
01:29:42,494 --> 01:29:44,186
Where are you?

1921
01:29:45,662 --> 01:29:48,695
Is that from a movie
or did I just make that up?

1922
01:29:48,796 --> 01:29:50,399
It's pretty good.

1923
01:29:50,500 --> 01:29:52,620
- There he is!
- You can use it if you want.

1924
01:29:55,539 --> 01:29:56,965
No, please…

1925
01:29:57,066 --> 01:29:59,101
For what it's worth,
I'm still in love with you.

1926
01:30:00,709 --> 01:30:02,807
And I don't think you should
give up on that happy ending.

1927
01:30:02,908 --> 01:30:04,106
Colt.

1928
01:30:05,010 --> 01:30:06,613
I got to go.

1929
01:30:06,714 --> 01:30:07,646
Colt.

