01:33:39,636 --> 01:33:41,186
the suicide of American stunt…

1976
01:33:42,517 --> 01:33:44,270
Following a dramatic boat explosion…

1977
01:33:44,371 --> 01:33:46,123
on Sydney Harbour, police are…

1978
01:33:46,224 --> 01:33:49,699
Following a dramatic boat
explosion on Sydney Harbour…

1979
01:33:49,800 --> 01:33:51,293
police are currently investigating…

1980
01:33:51,394 --> 01:33:53,195
the suicide of
American stuntman Colt Seavers.

1981
01:33:54,969 --> 01:33:56,938
Jody, you need
to be quiet. Don't say a word.

1982
01:34:11,515 --> 01:34:13,118
Wait, wait. No.

1983
01:34:22,294 --> 01:34:24,162
Jody…

1984
01:34:34,779 --> 01:34:39,276
You think you can come
to my set and sneak up on me?

1985
01:34:46,021 --> 01:34:47,383
Wait!

1986
01:34:49,728 --> 01:34:51,519
It's me. It's me.

1987
01:34:52,863 --> 01:34:54,796
Remember?

1988
01:34:54,897 --> 01:34:56,560
Jesus Christ.

1989
01:34:56,661 --> 01:34:58,325
I knew it.

1990
01:34:58,426 --> 01:34:59,526
I knew it.

1991
01:35:00,802 --> 01:35:02,736
I knew you were alive.

1992
01:35:02,837 --> 01:35:03,836
Three shows a day…

1993
01:35:03,937 --> 01:35:05,321
six days a week for three years.

1994
01:35:05,422 --> 01:35:06,907
The <i>Miami Vice</i> stunt show.

1995
01:35:08,339 --> 01:35:09,611
You remembered.

1996
01:35:09,712 --> 01:35:11,976
Yes. I'm happy you're alive, Colt.

1997
01:35:12,077 --> 01:35:14,342
Colt, I'm so happy you're alive.

1998
01:35:14,443 --> 01:35:15,881
- I knew it.
- Oh, my God.

1999
01:35:15,982 --> 01:35:17,718
- What were you doing…
- Nice work with the pen.

2000
01:35:17,819 --> 01:35:19,083
- So sorry.
- No, it was great. You got it out just in time.

2001
01:35:19,184 --> 01:35:21,151
I think the ink poisoning didn't set in.

2002
01:35:21,252 --> 01:35:23,218
- Chef's kiss.
- What's going on?

2003
01:35:23,319 --> 01:35:25,089
- Huh?
- Everyone's saying that you killed Henry.

2004
01:35:25,190 --> 01:35:27,256
Ryder killed Henry. He framed me.

2005
01:35:27,357 --> 01:35:28,553
There's footage of you.

2006
01:35:28,654 --> 01:35:30,456
- Well, he deepfaked me.
- What?

2007
01:35:30,557 --> 01:35:32,524
They do it all the time on the Internet.

2008
01:35:32,625 --> 01:35:35,132
They take Tom Cruise's face,
and they put it on yours.

2009
01:35:35,233 --> 01:35:36,551
And you can't tell the difference.

2010
01:35:36,652 --> 01:35:38,245
No. Okay, so where's the real footage…

2011
01:35:38,346 --> 01:35:39,937
of Ryder killing Henry?
How do we get it?

2012
01:35:40,038 --> 01:35:41,873
It was on Ryder's phone, and
then it got destroyed because…

2013
01:35:41,974 --> 01:35:44,392
- Dan's <i>Last of the Mohicans</i> plan didn't work out.
- What?

2014
01:35:44,493 --> 01:35:46,912
It's not his fault, you know?
He called tomahawk first, okay.

2015
01:35:47,013 --> 01:35:48,275
I got "blanks only."

2016
01:35:48,376 --> 01:35:49,541
And it was going pretty well, actually…

2017
01:35:49,642 --> 01:35:51,377
and then Dressler showed up.

2018
01:35:51,478 --> 01:35:54,216
So he, you know, he does this,
like, Jason Bourne shit.

2019
01:35:54,317 --> 01:35:56,790
Okay, I have so many questions.

2020
01:35:56,891 --> 01:35:58,285
Okay.

2021
01:35:58,386 --> 01:36:00,288
Who else knows you're alive?

2022
01:36:00,389 --> 01:36:02,058
- No one.
- Great.

2023
01:36:02,159 --> 01:36:03,730
No, that's the point. I mean, I figure…

2024
01:36:03,831 --> 01:36:04,930
we can't finish the movie
unless they think I'm dead.

2025
01:36:05,031 --> 01:36:06,590
What movie?

2026
01:36:06,691 --> 01:36:07,635
<i>Metalstorm.</i>

2027
01:36:07,736 --> 01:36:09,395
What about <i>Metalstorm?</i>

2028
01:36:09,496 --> 01:36:10,804
If they think I'm dead,
they'll come back and finish.

2029
01:36:10,905 --> 01:36:11,969
- Who?
- Ryder.

2030
01:36:12,070 --> 01:36:13,487
- Finish what?
- The movie.

2031
01:36:13,588 --> 01:36:15,005
<i>- Metalstorm?</i>
- Exactly.

2032
01:36:15,106 --> 01:36:16,655
- Are you insane? You are insane.
- What?

2033
01:36:16,756 --> 01:36:18,063
You need to be
burning your fingerprints off…

2034
01:36:18,164 --> 01:36:19,472
and you need to be
getting across the border…

2035
01:36:19,573 --> 01:36:21,176
as fast as possible.

2036
01:36:21,277 --> 01:36:23,309
We're gonna hide you
until we can clear your name.

2037
01:36:23,410 --> 01:36:25,444
None of it matters anymore.
It's just a stupid movie.

2038
01:36:25,545 --> 01:36:26,511
- What?
- It's a stupid movie.

2039
01:36:26,612 --> 01:36:27,984
Don't say that.

2040
01:36:28,085 --> 01:36:30,580
That's <i>Metalstorm</i> you're talking about.

2041
01:36:30,681 --> 01:36:32,858
That's the movie you spent
your whole life trying to make.

2042
01:36:32,959 --> 01:36:34,518
Who knows?

2043
01:36:34,619 --> 01:36:36,521
You might inspire a whole
generation of little Jodys…

2044
01:36:36,622 --> 01:36:39,932
to pick up cameras
and make their own movies.

2045
01:36:41,936 --> 01:36:43,936
You're just… you're special.

2046
01:36:45,104 --> 01:36:47,202
And all of us get to be
a part of something special…

2047
01:36:47,303 --> 01:36:49,467
because it comes from you.

2048
01:36:49,568 --> 01:36:52,845
I obviously failed
at getting us our happy ending…

2049
01:36:52,946 --> 01:36:54,604
but I'll be damned if I'm gonna let…

2050
01:36:54,705 --> 01:36:56,784
Space Cowboy and Aliena
not have theirs.

2051
01:37:02,801 --> 01:37:04,350
Jody, my love!

2052
01:37:04,451 --> 01:37:05,686
- One sec!
- I'm coming…

2053
01:37:05,787 --> 01:37:07,023
Stop it.

2054
01:37:07,124 --> 01:37:08,552
Gail. She's in on it.

2055
01:37:08,653 --> 01:37:10,223
- What?
- Yes.

2056
01:37:10,324 --> 01:37:12,027
- Okay, come on.
- Let's just kiss a little bit first.

2057
01:37:12,128 --> 01:37:14,488
No, come on, we g… got to get
you in the bathroom, please.

2058
01:37:15,463 --> 01:37:16,693
Come on.

2059
01:37:18,301 --> 01:37:19,969
Come on.

2060
01:37:20,070 --> 01:37:22,467
Christ!

2061
01:37:22,568 --> 01:37:23,808
Got to work.

2062
01:37:23,909 --> 01:37:25,744
You all right in there, my darling?

2063
01:37:25,845 --> 01:37:28,309
Here, this… Take this soap
and rub it on my belly.

2064
01:37:30,181 --> 01:37:31,717
Get in the bedroom.

2065
01:37:31,818 --> 01:37:34,132
- Okay. Colt. Are you good? Okay.
- Okay. Yeah.

2066
01:37:34,233 --> 01:37:36,547
- Be quiet. Don't make a sound.
- Jod?

2067
01:37:36,648 --> 01:37:37,956
- My head. The head.
- What?

2068
01:37:40,453 --> 01:37:42,338
- Hi!
- Hey. Hello, you.

2069
01:37:42,439 --> 01:37:44,324
- Hey. Hey.
- Aw, come here.

2070
01:37:44,425 --> 01:37:45,731
Thank you.

2071
01:37:45,832 --> 01:37:47,145
Aw, how's my favorite director?

2072
01:37:47,246 --> 01:37:48,559
Uh, a bit emotional, you know.

2073
01:37:48,660 --> 01:37:50,064
Oh, no… Jesus.

2074
01:37:50,165 --> 01:37:51,692
Like Johnny and Amber
have just been here.

2075
01:37:51,793 --> 01:37:53,662
I just need to vent, 'cause it's been…

2076
01:37:53,763 --> 01:37:55,801
- it's just been so much.
- I know. I know.

2077
01:37:55,902 --> 01:37:57,940
- I'm so sorry about Colt.
- Thank you.

2078
01:37:58,041 --> 01:38:00,405
You know, it's such a shame,
but what a mess.

2079
01:38:00,506 --> 01:38:01,779
- Right.
- Who knew?

2080
01:38:01,880 --> 01:38:03,671
- Yeah.
- I mean, I tried to help him.

2081
01:38:03,772 --> 01:38:06,114
I hope you know that, but
sometimes you can't help people…

2082
01:38:06,215 --> 01:38:07,577
- who don't want to be saved.
- Right.

2083
01:38:07,678 --> 01:38:10,018
But silver lining…

2084
01:38:10,119 --> 01:38:13,055
to this very dark cloud.

2085
01:38:13,156 --> 01:38:14,787
I've got Ryder to come back.

2086
01:38:14,888 --> 01:38:16,654
- And I have a plan.
- Really?

2087
01:38:16,755 --> 01:38:18,521
But we're not gonna be able to do…

2088
01:38:18,622 --> 01:38:21,392
your big third act set piece, the car jump.

2089
01:38:21,493 --> 01:38:24,528
It is an impossible jump,
especially now with Colt gone.

2090
01:38:24,629 --> 01:38:26,595
- Dead.
- He's gone.

2091
01:38:26,696 --> 01:38:28,807
- He's so dead.
- Stay with me.

2092
01:38:28,908 --> 01:38:30,302
I spoke to Venti.

2093
01:38:30,403 --> 01:38:32,238
She says that she can do it in VFX.

2094
01:38:32,339 --> 01:38:33,634
The car jump.

2095
01:38:33,735 --> 01:38:35,912
All we need to focus on is Ryder's new…

2096
01:38:36,013 --> 01:38:39,410
final, bombastic monologue.

2097
01:38:39,511 --> 01:38:40,784
I've read the pages.

2098
01:38:40,885 --> 01:38:42,302
God, you smashed it. I knew you would.

2099
01:38:42,403 --> 01:38:43,821
- We're gonna get him covered.
- Yeah.

2100
01:38:43,922 --> 01:38:46,482
You, meanwhile…

2101
01:38:46,583 --> 01:38:49,403
please go and rest up in Fiji, on me.

2102
01:38:49,504 --> 01:38:52,323
You know? Plop yourself on a beach.

2103
01:38:52,424 --> 01:38:54,755
And I'm gonna take care
of all of it for you.

2104
01:38:54,856 --> 01:38:55,799
Gail.

2105
01:38:55,900 --> 01:38:57,328
You've got so much to process.

2106
01:38:57,429 --> 01:38:59,067
- No.
- I can take care of all of it.

2107
01:38:59,168 --> 01:39:01,596
No. This is my movie.

2108
01:39:01,697 --> 01:39:03,180
Now, listen to me.

2109
01:39:03,281 --> 01:39:04,764
I've learned so much from you.

2110
01:39:04,865 --> 01:39:07,438
- I know. Thank you.
- And I'm very grateful.

2111
01:39:07,539 --> 01:39:09,571
But the lesson I stand by now…

2112
01:39:09,672 --> 01:39:12,173
- that you've taught me…
- Yeah. Yeah.

2113
01:39:12,274 --> 01:39:14,875
You fall down, you get right back up.

2114
01:39:17,877 --> 01:39:19,531
I am directing this movie, yeah.

2115
01:39:19,632 --> 01:39:21,285
Oh, my God, that's my girl.

2116
01:39:21,386 --> 01:39:23,018
- It went in. I'm so proud of you.
- Good. Okay.

2117
01:39:23,119 --> 01:39:24,751
Thank you. All right,
let's get you out of here.

2118
01:39:24,852 --> 01:39:26,587
- One last thing.
- Yeah?

2119
01:39:26,688 --> 01:39:28,260
- Have you seen Dan?
- Nope. I think he's by the taco truck.

2120
01:39:28,361 --> 01:39:29,690
- You haven't heard from him?
- He's probably-probably…

2121
01:39:29,791 --> 01:39:30,966
over there somewhere.
Thank you so much.

2122
01:39:31,067 --> 01:39:32,527
- I'm proud of you.
- Thank you.

2123
01:39:32,628 --> 01:39:34,002
Thanks for the pep talk. Okay, buh-bye.

2124
01:39:34,103 --> 01:39:35,102
- Love you, darling.
- Love you, too. Bye!

2125
01:39:35,203 --> 01:39:37,004
Oof.

2126
01:39:37,105 --> 01:39:39,089
You're gonna finish the movie.

2127
01:39:39,190 --> 01:39:41,174
No, I'm gonna clear your name.
Okay, now listen.

2128
01:39:41,275 --> 01:39:42,373
Why can't we do both?

2129
01:39:42,474 --> 01:39:43,472
I think we can.

2130
01:39:43,573 --> 01:39:45,276
We're gonna bring him to set…

2131
01:39:45,377 --> 01:39:48,313
in a controlled environment,
and then we surround him…

2132
01:39:48,414 --> 01:39:50,777
And we beat the shit out of him.

2133
01:39:50,878 --> 01:39:52,283
No.

2134
01:39:52,384 --> 01:39:54,121
We're gonna force
a confession out of him…

2135
01:39:54,222 --> 01:39:56,122
by putting him in a scene.

2136
01:39:56,223 --> 01:39:57,718
- Right.
- You know, he always forgets he's mic'd.

2137
01:39:57,819 --> 01:39:59,190
That's better.

2138
01:39:59,291 --> 01:40:00,754
I just don't know how to do it yet.

2139
01:40:04,496 --> 01:40:06,001
I know how to do that.

2140
01:40:08,203 --> 01:40:10,301
Make him do his own stunt.

2141
01:40:10,402 --> 01:40:11,906
The impossible jump.

2142
01:40:12,007 --> 01:40:14,759
Then we beat the shit out of him.

2143
01:40:14,860 --> 01:40:17,713
One seventy-four, alpha, take two.

2144
01:40:20,776 --> 01:40:22,379
And action!

2145
01:40:22,480 --> 01:40:24,184
O-One second, one second, one second.

2146
01:40:26,947 --> 01:40:28,766
Action!

2147
01:40:30,586 --> 01:40:32,102
It's high noon…

2148
01:40:32,203 --> 01:40:33,820
at the edge of the universe, folks.

2149
01:40:49,804 --> 01:40:52,805
Now, we're facing a powerful enemy.

2150
01:40:54,314 --> 01:40:58,876
An alien species born of
the worst of humanity's traits.

2151
01:40:58,977 --> 01:41:02,297
Well, what our enemy doesn't see…

2152
01:41:02,398 --> 01:41:05,818
is that their demise is imminent.

2153
01:41:06,854 --> 01:41:11,760
And the most powerful weapon
in all galaxy?

2154
01:41:14,829 --> 01:41:16,763
Love.

2155
01:41:18,272 --> 01:41:24,769
Inside each and every
one of you is a spark, baby.

2156
01:41:24,870 --> 01:41:26,539
An ember.

2157
01:41:26,640 --> 01:41:29,208
A goddamn fire!

2158
01:41:32,879 --> 01:41:35,533
Love is how we will win.

2159
01:41:35,634 --> 01:41:38,287
And even if we lose…

2160
01:41:38,388 --> 01:41:42,094
we're gonna die
fighting for a happy ending!

2161
01:41:42,195 --> 01:41:45,328
Hell yeah!

2162
01:41:45,429 --> 01:41:46,922
Whoo!

2163
01:41:47,023 --> 01:41:48,925
Well, let's go and get it, then!

2164
01:41:49,026 --> 01:41:51,894
Get on out there and go!

2165
01:41:51,995 --> 01:41:54,799
Who's with me?
Who is with me? Let's go!

2166
01:41:54,900 --> 01:41:56,767
Cut! Yes!

2167
01:41:56,868 --> 01:41:58,802
So good, so good.

2168
01:41:58,903 --> 01:42:00,145
- Thank you.
- Was that it?

2169
01:42:00,246 --> 01:42:01,542
- God, yeah.
- Did we get it?

2170
01:42:01,643 --> 01:42:02,938
- It was so good.
- We got it?

2171
01:42:03,039 --> 01:42:04,347
- Magic. Yeah, yeah.
- Yeah, it was hot, babe.

2172
01:42:04,448 --> 01:42:06,018
Oh, my God. Gail was in floods.

2173
01:42:06,119 --> 01:42:07,679
I really felt that one.
I really felt that one.

2174
01:42:07,780 --> 01:42:09,285
- She was… Of course you did.
- 'Cause I had tears.

2175
01:42:09,386 --> 01:42:10,846
Of course you did.
Yeah, I know. I can see them.

2176
01:42:10,947 --> 01:42:12,832
Yeah, it was fantastic.

2177
01:42:12,933 --> 01:42:14,818
So, listen, all we have left
is the alien truck coverage.

2178
01:42:14,919 --> 01:42:16,258
- All right? That's it.
- No.

2179
01:42:16,359 --> 01:42:17,952
- Yep. We're gonna do the car jump.
- No.

2180
01:42:18,053 --> 01:42:19,707
- No one told me about another setup.
- We said… No.

2181
01:42:19,808 --> 01:42:21,503
- There's another setup?
- Venti's gonna do that in VFX…

2182
01:42:21,604 --> 01:42:23,182
- so we're out of here.
- I know, but we need his close-up.

2183
01:42:23,283 --> 01:42:24,861
All right? I need his close-up
right here for the coverage.

2184
01:42:24,962 --> 01:42:26,005
All right? 15 minutes tops.
That's all I need.

2185
01:42:26,106 --> 01:42:27,599
This is the bit, do you remember…

2186
01:42:27,700 --> 01:42:29,134
- where Space Cowboy steals the alien vehicle?
- Hmm.

2187
01:42:29,235 --> 01:42:30,669
- Come on. This is his moment.
- Wait, wait, wait, wait.

2188
01:42:30,770 --> 01:42:32,137
I'm not gonna do any driving, right?

2189
01:42:32,238 --> 01:42:33,606
Because I'm gonna feel really nauseous.

2190
01:42:33,707 --> 01:42:34,870
It's a blue screen setup.

2191
01:42:34,971 --> 01:42:37,116
I need this. I need this, okay?

2192
01:42:38,108 --> 01:42:39,446
Zero notice here.

2193
01:42:39,547 --> 01:42:41,482
We're moving as fast
as we can, all right?

2194
01:42:41,583 --> 01:42:44,385
Everyone, double the pace, yes?

2195
01:42:44,486 --> 01:42:46,785
Use those muscles!
Yes, good! Thank you!

2196
01:42:51,494 --> 01:42:53,625
Everyone in position!

2197
01:42:53,726 --> 01:42:55,958
Light the pyro!

2198
01:42:57,203 --> 01:43:01,468
We need enough charges to blow
this canyon sky-high, people.

2199
01:43:01,569 --> 01:43:03,173
McCabe, where are we?

2200
01:43:03,274 --> 01:43:04,504
Going as fast as I can, Nige.

2201
01:43:04,605 --> 01:43:05,939
We're as ready as we can be.

2202
01:43:06,040 --> 01:43:07,374
Okay. Hey, get Ray to come in…

2203
01:43:07,475 --> 01:43:09,310
- and check the mic before we go, okay?
- Copy.

2204
01:43:09,411 --> 01:43:12,183
Sound, can you come down here
and check Ryder's mic, please?

2205
01:43:17,289 --> 01:43:18,748
All right, Tom. You ready?

2206
01:43:18,849 --> 01:43:20,420
- Yeah.
- Okay. Remember this bit?

2207
01:43:20,521 --> 01:43:21,653
- You're gonna be in the alien vehicle.
- Mm-hmm.

2208
01:43:21,754 --> 01:43:22,857
- Okay? Okay.
- Yep.

2209
01:43:22,958 --> 01:43:24,061
And with nowhere to go…

2210
01:43:24,162 --> 01:43:25,393
you're gonna jump the car
over the ravine.

2211
01:43:25,494 --> 01:43:27,229
So I just need a quick pop on you…

2212
01:43:27,330 --> 01:43:28,858
Space Cowboy ain't scared of no ravine.

2213
01:43:28,959 --> 01:43:30,727
- Of course he's not.
- So I'm thinking maybe just…

2214
01:43:30,828 --> 01:43:32,026
- a couple of reaction shots of me gritting my teeth.
- Yeah.

2215
01:43:32,127 --> 01:43:32,895
Like, "Goddamn." Something like that.

2216
01:43:32,996 --> 01:43:34,270
Yeah, yeah, yeah. Stoic.

2217
01:43:34,371 --> 01:43:35,770
- Yeah, yeah. I like it.
- All right?

2218
01:43:35,871 --> 01:43:37,271
- What do you think?
- I like it. Okay.

2219
01:43:37,372 --> 01:43:38,372
I think it's gonna be great.
Yeah, I love the choice.

2220
01:43:38,473 --> 01:43:39,669
All right, let's pop these on.

2221
01:43:39,770 --> 01:43:41,275
- Okay. What's this?
- There you go.

2222
01:43:41,376 --> 01:43:42,673
No, this is because
you've escaped the aliens.

2223
01:43:42,774 --> 01:43:43,756
Is this necessary? It's a bit much, no?

2224
01:43:43,857 --> 01:43:44,840
Yeah. It looks cool. Raise the stakes.

2225
01:43:44,941 --> 01:43:46,577
It's kind of cool.

2226
01:43:46,678 --> 01:43:47,980
- Yeah. It's cool. Okay.
- Raise the stakes.

2227
01:43:48,081 --> 01:43:49,383
- Let's do it.
- 'Cause you know, Space Cowboy.

2228
01:43:49,484 --> 01:43:51,186
Nobody can get at the Space Cowboy.

2229
01:43:51,287 --> 01:43:52,881
- No way. Even when he's cuffed.
- Excuse me. Tom, sorry.

2230
01:43:52,982 --> 01:43:54,520
Jesus, Ray. I told you
to do it before I got on set.

2231
01:43:54,621 --> 01:43:56,225
Appreciate you, Tom.

2232
01:43:56,326 --> 01:43:57,341
Thank you. Sound good.

2233
01:43:57,442 --> 01:43:58,458
- Okay.
- Okay, great.

2234
01:43:58,559 --> 01:43:59,920
- So…
- So…

2235
01:44:00,021 --> 01:44:01,230
- You got this guy coming on your left.
- Yep.

2236
01:44:01,331 --> 01:44:02,791
- Hey, bro.
- All right, take him out.

2237
01:44:02,892 --> 01:44:03,793
Someone else is gonna
crash down on the bonnet.

2238
01:44:03,894 --> 01:44:05,464
You're gonna take him out.

2239
01:44:05,565 --> 01:44:07,203
No, no, no. See, what I'm
thinking is maybe I come down…

2240
01:44:07,304 --> 01:44:09,799
I take him out first,
and I'm like "pow, pow, pow."

2241
01:44:09,900 --> 01:44:11,751
- I slide over and go "pow."
- Yeah. Yeah.

2242
01:44:11,852 --> 01:44:13,703
And then maybe I say a little line like…

2243
01:44:13,804 --> 01:44:16,806
"I was shooting aliens
way before I was paid to."

2244
01:44:16,907 --> 01:44:18,872
Fantastic. All right, let's lock it up.

2245
01:44:18,973 --> 01:44:20,875
- Let's shoot, Nigel.
- Standing by, please.

2246
01:44:20,976 --> 01:44:22,129
All right.

2247
01:44:22,230 --> 01:44:23,382
Take one. Marker.

2248
01:44:23,483 --> 01:44:25,831
In three, two, one, action.

2249
01:44:28,180 --> 01:44:29,653
Not your lucky day, alien.

2250
01:44:29,754 --> 01:44:31,524
You got to go.

2251
01:44:32,593 --> 01:44:34,312
You can't outrun me.

2252
01:44:34,413 --> 01:44:36,132
I'm Space Cowboy!

2253
01:44:36,233 --> 01:44:37,264
Yahoo!

2254
01:44:37,365 --> 01:44:38,766
You are approaching the ravine.

2255
01:44:38,867 --> 01:44:40,267
There's nowhere else to go.

2256
01:44:40,368 --> 01:44:42,061
Turn right. Go on.

2257
01:44:42,162 --> 01:44:43,402
You have no choice.

2258
01:44:43,503 --> 01:44:44,404
You're gonna have to make the jump.

2259
01:44:44,505 --> 01:44:47,407
In three, two, one.

2260
01:44:47,508 --> 01:44:50,739
Yeehaw!

2261
01:44:50,840 --> 01:44:52,280
Whoa, whoa, whoa, hey, hey, hey.

2262
01:44:52,381 --> 01:44:53,907
Who is that in the car with him?

2263
01:44:54,008 --> 01:44:56,581
We're-we're in the middle
of a take right now, asshole.

2264
01:44:56,682 --> 01:44:58,417
What are you doing? Ah!

2265
01:44:58,518 --> 01:45:00,486
- He's just buckling you in. Safety first. That's it.
- Ow!

2266
01:45:00,587 --> 01:45:02,784
It's really tight. Is this necessary?

2267
01:45:02,885 --> 01:45:04,885
Hey, we are filming right now.

2268
01:45:04,986 --> 01:45:06,985
Keep rolling, keep rolling.

2269
01:45:07,086 --> 01:45:08,427
Sell it, Tom. It looks amazing.
Take a deep breath.

2270
01:45:08,528 --> 01:45:10,727
It does not look… Get out of the car.

2271
01:45:11,928 --> 01:45:13,024
Howdy.

2272
01:45:13,125 --> 01:45:15,094
No, no, wait. Stop. No.

2273
01:45:16,064 --> 01:45:17,029
Wait, what's happening?

2274
01:45:17,130 --> 01:45:18,931
Yeehaw!

2275
01:45:19,032 --> 01:45:21,132
Oh, my God! Whoa!

2276
01:45:21,233 --> 01:45:23,476
Get to the cars!

2277
01:45:26,446 --> 01:45:28,039
Jody, what the hell are you doing?

2278
01:45:28,140 --> 01:45:29,041
I'm trying to get something
real out of him, Gail.

2279
01:45:29,142 --> 01:45:30,450
There's no cameras on him!

2280
01:45:32,685 --> 01:45:35,619
Hey, Dan? They're approaching
Ambush Alley right now.

2281
01:45:35,720 --> 01:45:37,154
We're ready.

2282
01:45:38,590 --> 01:45:41,393
Let me out right now!

2283
01:45:41,494 --> 01:45:44,562
What are you gonna do, huh?
You gonna kill me? Again?

2284
01:45:49,536 --> 01:45:51,701
- Can you untie me?
- No.

2285
01:45:58,171 --> 01:45:59,674
McCabe!

2286
01:45:59,775 --> 01:46:03,250
Smoke screen in three, two, one!

2287
01:46:03,351 --> 01:46:05,174
Whoa!

2288
01:46:05,275 --> 01:46:07,211
This does not seem safe, man!

2289
01:46:12,691 --> 01:46:15,327
Dan, where are they?
Do you have eyes on them?

2290
01:46:15,428 --> 01:46:17,727
I see 'em. Everything's going to plan.

2291
01:46:20,468 --> 01:46:22,231
I'll block the road.

2292
01:46:22,332 --> 01:46:24,094
They shall not pass!

2293
01:46:24,195 --> 01:46:27,000
I see them.
They're entering Ambush Alley.

2294
01:46:31,643 --> 01:46:33,346
I can't see shit!

2295
01:46:35,141 --> 01:46:37,141
McCabe, one!

2296
01:46:38,078 --> 01:46:40,419
McCabe, two!

2297
01:46:44,237 --> 01:46:45,655
McCabe! Now!

2298
01:46:55,766 --> 01:46:57,337
I love my job.

2299
01:47:01,673 --> 01:47:05,377
Whoa, mama!

2300
01:47:05,478 --> 01:47:07,708
Oh, goddamn!

2301
01:47:07,809 --> 01:47:10,239
I can't think straight
when you drive like this.

2302
01:47:10,340 --> 01:47:11,744
You're supposed to be dead.

2303
01:47:11,845 --> 01:47:14,814
You blew up in-in a thousand pieces.

2304
01:47:14,915 --> 01:47:16,144
You went kaboom.

2305
01:47:16,245 --> 01:47:18,614
Why would I have blown up, Tom Ryder?

2306
01:47:18,715 --> 01:47:21,083
Why are you saying my name like that?

2307
01:47:21,184 --> 01:47:22,789
- That is your name, isn't it, Tom Ryder?
- Yes, yes.

2308
01:47:22,890 --> 01:47:24,295
A blind man could see that you're…

2309
01:47:24,396 --> 01:47:25,824
- Tom Ryder.
- You're saying that like…

2310
01:47:25,925 --> 01:47:27,398
- "Ryder, Tom Ryder."
- Okay. That's me.

2311
01:47:27,499 --> 01:47:28,663
You're saying it like
some obsessed fangirl.

2312
01:47:28,764 --> 01:47:30,158
That's me, Colt Seavers, saying that.

2313
01:47:30,259 --> 01:47:31,561
Roll the cameras.
We're heading for the jump.

2314
01:47:31,662 --> 01:47:32,964
Tom Ryder's doing his own stunts!

2315
01:47:33,065 --> 01:47:34,801
Everyone, roll. Arm car?

2316
01:47:34,902 --> 01:47:36,065
Check.

2317
01:47:36,166 --> 01:47:37,440
- Heli.
- Check.

2318
01:47:37,541 --> 01:47:38,969
I'm done taking the falls for you.

2319
01:47:39,070 --> 01:47:40,608
You're gonna do your own stunts
from now on.

2320
01:47:40,709 --> 01:47:42,423
- I don't want to do my own stunts, Colt!
- Relax.

2321
01:47:42,524 --> 01:47:44,601
It's just a 250-foot jump
that'll probably kill us.

2322
01:47:44,702 --> 01:47:46,779
It's never been done before.
It's for Comic-Con.

2323
01:47:46,880 --> 01:47:49,750
- It's Hall H. It's a big deal.
- What are you doing, man?

2324
01:47:49,851 --> 01:47:51,146
I thought it'd be fitting.

2325
01:47:51,247 --> 01:47:53,490
Me and you, Tom Ryder, one last stunt.

2326
01:47:53,591 --> 01:47:55,689
You know, like Thelma and Louise.

2327
01:47:55,790 --> 01:47:57,624
- Thelma and Louise?
- Yeah.

2328
01:47:57,725 --> 01:47:59,858
- They die at the end.
- Exactly!

2329
01:47:59,959 --> 01:48:01,760
Murder-suicide.

2330
01:48:01,861 --> 01:48:03,830
Can you just pull over
and let me out right now?

2331
01:48:05,130 --> 01:48:07,503
You're not getting
out of this car until you…

2332
01:48:07,604 --> 01:48:09,933
Tom Ryder, tell me,
Colt Seavers, the truth!

2333
01:48:10,034 --> 01:48:11,034
All right, all right, all right, all right!

2334
01:48:11,135 --> 01:48:12,606
It was all Gail.

2335
01:48:12,707 --> 01:48:14,609
When I killed Henry,
she wanted to cover it up…

2336
01:48:14,710 --> 01:48:16,137
because, to be honest…

2337
01:48:16,238 --> 01:48:18,646
Space Cowboy's one of
my best roles yet, Colt…

2338
01:48:18,747 --> 01:48:20,307
and I don't want this movie to fail.

2339
01:48:20,408 --> 01:48:21,978
So you're saying that Gail Meyer…

2340
01:48:22,079 --> 01:48:25,048
was responsible for framing me
for your murder of Henry?

2341
01:48:25,149 --> 01:48:26,950
Yes! Yes!

2342
01:48:27,051 --> 01:48:28,722
But what's your real name?

2343
01:48:28,823 --> 01:48:30,428
Tom Ryder.

2344
01:48:31,497 --> 01:48:33,309
Did you get that, Jody?

2345
01:48:33,410 --> 01:48:35,222
We got it! He confessed.

2346
01:48:35,323 --> 01:48:36,862
You wearing a wire?
Bro, you recording this?

2347
01:48:36,963 --> 01:48:38,565
This is entrapment. You can't do that.

2348
01:48:38,666 --> 01:48:40,194
- What are you doing?
- No, it's not entrapment…

2349
01:48:40,295 --> 01:48:42,868
because you're wearing the wire, dipshit!

2350
01:48:46,971 --> 01:48:48,202
He's going for it. Go. Go now.

2351
01:48:48,303 --> 01:48:49,709
I'm just an actor!

2352
01:48:49,810 --> 01:48:51,006
Wait.

2353
01:48:51,107 --> 01:48:52,843
He has a mouth guard.

2354
01:48:52,944 --> 01:48:55,518
I don't have a mouth guard.

2355
01:49:43,358 --> 01:49:45,225
- Oh, good.
- Colt!

2356
01:49:45,326 --> 01:49:47,800
- You're alive.
- Are you okay?

2357
01:49:49,164 --> 01:49:50,537
Are you okay?

2358
01:49:50,638 --> 01:49:52,265
I told you I'd make the camera up to you.

2359
01:49:52,366 --> 01:49:54,068
Oh, it was fantastic.

2360
01:49:54,169 --> 01:49:55,740
- Dressler, come in!
- Ah!

2361
01:49:55,841 --> 01:49:57,726
Oy, can you hear me?
We've got to get out of here!

2362
01:49:57,827 --> 01:49:59,712
This is all Gail's fault, man.

2363
01:49:59,813 --> 01:50:01,306
This is all Gail's idea.

2364
01:50:01,407 --> 01:50:02,715
- Give me that confession!
- No.

2365
01:50:02,816 --> 01:50:04,583
Give me all the media! Are you deaf?

2366
01:50:04,684 --> 01:50:07,554
Dressler, bring
the helicopter to the trench.

2367
01:50:07,655 --> 01:50:08,753
- What about Ryder?
- Now!

2368
01:50:08,854 --> 01:50:10,380
Now, about this date.

2369
01:50:10,481 --> 01:50:12,955
Put it in the case, you numpty!

2370
01:50:13,056 --> 01:50:14,285
Can we call it a date?

2371
01:50:14,386 --> 01:50:17,322
I mean, that's what it is, right?

2372
01:50:17,423 --> 01:50:18,533
Such a moron!

2373
01:50:19,459 --> 01:50:22,294
- Hurry up! God!
- - Take it.

2374
01:50:22,395 --> 01:50:24,130
Gail, Gail, Gail.

2375
01:50:24,231 --> 01:50:26,633
- Listen…
- Give me the recording, Gail.

2376
01:50:26,734 --> 01:50:29,138
Darling, calm down. Just come with me.

2377
01:50:29,239 --> 01:50:31,644
We don't need all this toxic masculinity…

2378
01:50:31,745 --> 01:50:33,074
because we're the same, you and me.

2379
01:50:33,175 --> 01:50:34,910
You know, we're survivors.

2380
01:50:35,011 --> 01:50:36,648
No, no, no, no. I'm nothing like you.

2381
01:50:36,749 --> 01:50:39,233
I don't want to be presumptuous, I mean…

2382
01:50:39,334 --> 01:50:41,819
but let's call a spade a spade.

2383
01:50:41,920 --> 01:50:43,485
That's why I gave you the job.

2384
01:50:43,586 --> 01:50:45,974
- Okay.
- Well, that and because…

2385
01:50:46,075 --> 01:50:48,562
you're so easily moldable, you know?

2386
01:50:49,422 --> 01:50:51,828
- Oh!
- Gail, just give me the case!

2387
01:50:51,929 --> 01:50:53,698
This is a Gail Meyer production!

2388
01:50:53,799 --> 01:50:55,325
Not yours!

2389
01:50:55,426 --> 01:50:57,460
Rendezvous with the boss in the canyon.

2390
01:50:57,561 --> 01:50:58,769
Extraction to the spaceship set.

2391
01:50:58,870 --> 01:51:00,886
Spaceship set?

2392
01:51:00,987 --> 01:51:03,003
Oh, no, Big Red.

2393
01:51:03,104 --> 01:51:05,170
I don't think you're gonna make that one.

2394
01:51:05,271 --> 01:51:07,338
- Stunts set!
- Stunts set!

2395
01:51:07,439 --> 01:51:09,649
Go!

2396
01:51:22,323 --> 01:51:24,828
Trust me, I will not
be taking the fall for this…

2397
01:51:24,929 --> 01:51:29,898
because I deliver hits
for all you little people.

2398
01:51:29,999 --> 01:51:30,964
You're welcome.

2399
01:51:31,065 --> 01:51:34,034
Whoa!

2400
01:51:34,135 --> 01:51:35,432
Jody?

2401
01:51:38,536 --> 01:51:41,173
- Jody?
- Hey, hey! That's for me! That's for me!

2402
01:51:41,274 --> 01:51:43,378
That's my helicopter!

2403
01:51:43,479 --> 01:51:45,684
This crazy stuntman's lost his mind!

2404
01:51:59,524 --> 01:52:00,864
I'm on vacation!

2405
01:52:14,206 --> 01:52:16,340
Get this dog off me! Not again, dog.

2406
01:52:17,717 --> 01:52:18,914
Just stay there!

2407
01:52:20,016 --> 01:52:22,753
Night-night, dog! You're dead.

2408
01:52:33,557 --> 01:52:36,162
This design is growing on me.

2409
01:52:37,561 --> 01:52:40,017
Get in! Let's get out of here!

2410
01:52:40,118 --> 01:52:42,674
Yeah, copy that. Taking off now.

2411
01:52:44,205 --> 01:52:45,533
Wait, what-what is this?

2412
01:52:45,634 --> 01:52:46,874
It's the evidence!

2413
01:52:46,975 --> 01:52:48,712
Why didn't you just stop talking?

2414
01:52:48,813 --> 01:52:50,108
Jody!

2415
01:52:50,209 --> 01:52:52,210
Blow the pyros. Blow the pyros!

2416
01:52:52,311 --> 01:52:54,015
They're getting away!

2417
01:52:57,888 --> 01:52:59,820
- Whoa! Sh… Whoa!
- Holy shit!

2418
01:52:59,921 --> 01:53:02,252
- Lower the arm! I'm gonna jump.
- Okay.

2419
01:53:02,353 --> 01:53:04,453
Okay, lower the arm. Lower the arm.

2420
01:53:08,525 --> 01:53:10,292
I have a plan!

2421
01:53:10,393 --> 01:53:12,229
What is it? What's-what's the plan?

2422
01:53:12,330 --> 01:53:13,262
Get me to the helicopter.

2423
01:53:13,363 --> 01:53:14,736
I'm gonna jump onto the skids…

2424
01:53:14,837 --> 01:53:15,771
and then I'm gonna
beat the shit out of him.

2425
01:53:15,872 --> 01:53:17,235
No, just-just get the recording.

2426
01:53:31,449 --> 01:53:32,723
Go!

2427
01:53:33,319 --> 01:53:34,317
Ah, shit.

2428
01:53:34,418 --> 01:53:35,726
Go!

2429
01:53:36,795 --> 01:53:39,322
Whoa! Whoa! Get me down!

2430
01:53:39,423 --> 01:53:41,025
Whoa! Get me down!

2431
01:53:41,126 --> 01:53:42,291
We're losing hydraulics here.

2432
01:53:42,392 --> 01:53:43,590
I can't get it under control.

2433
01:53:44,802 --> 01:53:46,426
Just wondering,
you know, after this movie…

2434
01:53:46,527 --> 01:53:49,430
and if I don't go to prison
and, you know, you're not busy…

2435
01:53:49,531 --> 01:53:51,465
maybe we could go
to a beach somewhere.

2436
01:53:51,566 --> 01:53:53,499
Wear a couple of swimming costumes.

2437
01:53:53,600 --> 01:53:55,721
Just drink a spicy margarita
or something.

2438
01:53:55,822 --> 01:53:57,944
- Yeah, yeah. Make some bad decisions.
- Yeah.

2439
01:53:58,045 --> 01:53:59,538
Okay, sure. Yes.

2440
01:53:59,639 --> 01:54:01,145
- Sound like a plan?
- It's a better plan than this.

2441
01:54:01,246 --> 01:54:03,031
Okay, please be careful.

2442
01:54:03,132 --> 01:54:05,018
Okay, swing him around. Go!

2443
01:54:22,367 --> 01:54:24,364
God, get it under control!

2444
01:54:24,465 --> 01:54:26,665
Get us out of here! What are you doing?

2445
01:54:32,737 --> 01:54:34,474
Ryder, the confession!

2446
01:54:34,575 --> 01:54:35,881
No!

2447
01:54:35,982 --> 01:54:37,984
- No! No, Gail, no!
- - No, Gail!

2448
01:54:40,449 --> 01:54:42,054
Whoa! Whoa!

2449
01:54:43,816 --> 01:54:45,484
Stunts!

2450
01:54:45,585 --> 01:54:47,652
Mobilize that airbag now!

2451
01:54:47,753 --> 01:54:49,093
No!

2452
01:54:52,561 --> 01:54:54,396
Get out of the way, Ryder!

2453
01:54:56,664 --> 01:54:59,004
87North to the rescue!

2454
01:54:59,105 --> 01:55:00,775
- Go, go, go, go!
- Go!

2455
01:55:00,876 --> 01:55:02,734
Move, move, move!

2456
01:55:04,309 --> 01:55:05,473
Get it!

2457
01:55:07,575 --> 01:55:09,146
Just keep it steady!

2458
01:55:10,379 --> 01:55:11,819
You moron!

2459
01:55:21,193 --> 01:55:23,589
Yes! Nice!

2460
01:55:26,902 --> 01:55:28,660
Go, go, go!

2461
01:55:40,014 --> 01:55:41,882
Yes!

2462
01:55:42,841 --> 01:55:44,181
- Oh, God!
- Oh, shit!

2463
01:55:47,450 --> 01:55:49,086
No!

2464
01:55:49,187 --> 01:55:50,686
Grab it!

2465
01:55:52,188 --> 01:55:53,388
Oh, my God! My nose!

2466
01:55:57,360 --> 01:56:00,130
No! Ryder, the gun!

2467
